      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776086798719,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "China’s system shouldn’t be called ‘Communist’ anymore.\nIt’s not fully capitalist either.  It’s a third way: State-controlled capitalism with Chinese characteristics — where the Party picks winners, crushes losers, and keeps all real power.  Neither Marx nor Adam Smith. Just raw pragmatism wrapped in red flag\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "China’s system shouldn’t be called ‘Communist’ anymore.\nIt’s not fully capitalist either.  It’s a third way: State-controlled capitalism with Chinese characteristics — where the Party picks winners, crushes losers, and keeps all real power.  Neither Marx nor Adam Smith. Just raw pragmatism wrapped in red flag\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
